ilities pretty well. My younger brother Madrim knows basically what he can and is expected to do. What he doesn't know, he'll learn. As will I, as I gain in experience and ability.<br>
Now to what I'm wondering. What is it the rest of you do that aren't druids. I have a pretty good idea, but there are certain skills I hear about that I don't see used when I'm grouped with members of other classes. There are some used that I don't understand (in game mechanics. Sneak for example. What exactly does it do?) <br>
As raidmaster, I feel that this info might help me to better plan raids. I have a good idea what monks, SK's, rangers and warriors can do, and what their expected role should be. Wizards, I'm pretty sure of as well. An enchanter's role is self-explanatory if you've grouped with one? Er... a cleric's role is obvious, but they may have stuff beyond what I can see in a group. As may the other classes I've mentioned. I have no idea what a rogue should do, other than backstab. What does and can a bard do? Paladins do what? They're decent tanks, but I'd prefer a warrior -as a healer- any day. Although a high-level pally can be almost as good as a cleric sometimes, hehe.<br>
I have limited experience grouping with diverse classes. I can count the times on one hand I've grouped with bards and rogues. I've grouped with a Shaman once. What is it that you guys do?<br>
