<br>
Bards - tank / buffer...  a bard can tank like a ranger, but their songs can be used during battle as well as buffers.  there are songs for healing, songs that work like breeze (commonly known as &quot;the mana song&quot; but which has a better name) as well as songs that make you stronger and faster and more.<br>
<br>
Pally's - tank / healer...  a pally's most valuable asset is the capability to perform a single full heal in an instant, no delay for casting and no mana...  they can taunt off the warrior and when they get beat down, fix it fast or even save the main tank from certain death when the cleric says oom...  it does have a 72 minute refresh time delay before it can be done again...<br>
<br>
Shaman - buffers / debuffers...  a shaman has excellent buff spells for the group members and debuffers for the target...  they can tank in a pinch and heal in a pinch as well...<br>
<br>
A rogue, though not a true tank can fill in if needed.  basically though (when skill gets high enough, they are damage doers like wizzies but at close range) A BS can do up to 1000 damage at higher levels and the poisons that can be applied to the weapons work like DoTs so a BS with poison can do upwards of 1200 HPs of damage at higher levels...   they also have a better sneak ability than the other classes which is very useful in corpse recovery if a battle went bad...<br>
