If I'm not the healer, then what? Am I the evac guy? I haven't been called on to do this yet, so if ya end up with me in a situation where we need one, be patient. I've done it twice, more importantly, I know how, but on the other side of the screen, I'm human. Practice will make perfect, just hopefully not dead, hehe.<br>
No evac likely to be needed? I'll throw damage shields barring the presence of a mage who has better. I'll ensnare. When I'm the healer, I leave this to rangers or sk's or necs, but I have the best snare out of all the classes. Next, I'll dot. I've got a couple mean ones that are stackable with most others. I understand that they pale in comparison to a nec/shaman dot, but they're stackable, so why not? <br>
I rarely nuke as ofttimes I have the role of backup healer. If a nuke will make a mob run, I'll throw one. Otherwise, I'll save my mana for a heal in case the main healer is OoM.<br>
I can be the puller. I really don't like to do this because it really really really really really pisses mobs off. I'll do it with a bad-azz tank, though, no problem.<br>
My buffs are decent. Chanters, clerics and shamen can all out-buff me, though. My buffs do stack well with most others I've seen, with the exception of the holy armor line, which my skin line will not stack with. My strength line of buffs seems to be stackable with shamen strength line, so as a buffing team, I think a shamen and druid would work well together. I may be wrong, though, as I have very rarely grouped or worked with a shaman.<br>
I'm probably missing something, as I always seem to have a different role, but like Bagum, did I just write a novel?<br>
<br>
